headline: Realtor.com速 Rent Report: U.S. Rental Market Now Firmly Renter-Friendly as Vacancy Rate Climbs to 7.6%
summary: The U.S. rental market has officially tipped in favor of tenants. According to the Realtor.com速 January Rental Report, the average rental vacancy rate across the nation's 50 largest metros climbed to 7.6% in 2025, a notable improvement from 7.2% in 2024. This surge in availability has transformed the market landscape: 44 out of the 50 largest metros are now either renter-friendly or balanced, leaving just six markets where landlords still hold the upper hand.
